Egypt Considering Holding Mubarak Trial in Cairo, Ahram Says

-- B y   M a r i a m   F a m
-- 
2011-07-28T07:50:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-28/egypt-considering-holding-mubarak-trial-in-cairo-ahram-says.html
Egyptian Justice Minister Mohamed el-Gendy has formed a committee to study whether an exhibition
center in Cairo can be used for the trial of former President
 Hosni Mubarak , the state-run Al Ahram newspaper  reported .  The trial of Mubarak, who is hospitalized in the Red Sea
resort of  Sharm el-Sheikh , and his two sons is scheduled to open
on Aug. 3 on charges of killing demonstrators and abusing public
office.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mariam Fam in Cairo at 
 mfam1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Louis Meixler at 
 lmeixler@bloomberg.net . 